<subSubSection pageId="3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,697,1046]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,697,722]" pageId="3">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Length 
<quantity box="[385,497,698,722]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="3" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.30 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[598,710,698,722]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="3" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.80 mm</quantity>
. Body slightly oval; with uniform, bristly, long, yellowish pubescence; integument dark, punctation dense (
<figureCitation box="[693,761,733,758]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1628,1650]" captionTargetBox="[151,1419,1093,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1093,1606]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Sidonis consanguinea (Mulsant, 1850). Lectotype from Musée des Confluences, Lyon, France (MNHL), 7. dorsal view, 8. lateral view, 9. frontal view, 10. abdomen, 11. labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1059309/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Head, antennae and mouthparts reddish (
<figureCitation box="[1237,1305,733,758]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1628,1650]" captionTargetBox="[151,1419,1093,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1093,1606]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Sidonis consanguinea (Mulsant, 1850). Lectotype from Musée des Confluences, Lyon, France (MNHL), 7. dorsal view, 8. lateral view, 9. frontal view, 10. abdomen, 11. labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1059309/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Pronotum dark greenish with two reddish lateral spots (
<figureCitation box="[650,718,769,794]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1628,1650]" captionTargetBox="[151,1419,1093,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1093,1606]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Sidonis consanguinea (Mulsant, 1850). Lectotype from Musée des Confluences, Lyon, France (MNHL), 7. dorsal view, 8. lateral view, 9. frontal view, 10. abdomen, 11. labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1059309/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Scutellar shield triangular, dark greenish. Elytra greenish, with an oblique reddish spot at apex (
<figureCitation box="[523,634,805,830]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1628,1650]" captionTargetBox="[151,1419,1093,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1093,1606]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Sidonis consanguinea (Mulsant, 1850). Lectotype from Musée des Confluences, Lyon, France (MNHL), 7. dorsal view, 8. lateral view, 9. frontal view, 10. abdomen, 11. labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1059309/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figs. 7–8</figureCitation>
). Differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Churata-Salcedo &amp; Almeida &amp; González &amp; Gordon" authorityYear="2017" box="[805,935,805,829]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Sidonis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biguttata">
<emphasis box="[805,935,805,829]" italics="true" pageId="3">S. biguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the lack of two small spots in middle of elytral length. Legs reddish with flattened femora and narrow tibiae. Abdomen with postcoxal lines reaching the posterior margin of the first ventrite (
<figureCitation box="[568,651,877,902]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1628,1650]" captionTargetBox="[151,1419,1093,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1093,1606]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Sidonis consanguinea (Mulsant, 1850). Lectotype from Musée des Confluences, Lyon, France (MNHL), 7. dorsal view, 8. lateral view, 9. frontal view, 10. abdomen, 11. labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1059309/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,697,1046]" box="[199,641,913,938]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,509,913,938]" pageId="3">Geographical distribution</emphasis>
. Colombia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,697,1046]" pageId="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,375,949,974]" pageId="3">
<typeStatus box="[199,258,949,974]" pageId="3">Type</typeStatus>
material.
</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[384,496,950,974]" pageId="3">Lectotype</typeStatus>
was labelled in 1970 by Gordon and deposited in Musée des Confluences, Lyon, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,227,986,1009]" name="France" pageId="3">France</collectingCountry>
(
<collectionCode box="[242,331,986,1010]" country="France" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/4jmm-iazx" name="Musee Guimet d'Histoire Naturelle de Lyon" pageId="3">MHNL</collectionCode>
). This designation was not published so we now designate this specimen as the 
<typeStatus box="[1226,1329,985,1010]" pageId="3">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1628,1650]" captionTargetBox="[151,1419,1093,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,1093,1606]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Sidonis consanguinea (Mulsant, 1850). Lectotype from Musée des Confluences, Lyon, France (MNHL), 7. dorsal view, 8. lateral view, 9. frontal view, 10. abdomen, 11. labels." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1059309/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figs. 7– 11</figureCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[252,355,1021,1046]" pageId="3">lectotype</typeStatus>
was studied from photographs.
</paragraph>
